SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYThursday 16 June S10 V1 Breidablik have made the perfect start to the new season in Iceland with eight wins from eight matches but that record comes under threat away at Valur tonight. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Botafogo vs Sao Paulo: Botafogo won their last clash against Sao Paulo last season which ended a run of six without success against them.M2 FH Hafnarfjörður vs Leiknir Reykjavik: FH have won all four previous home games against Leiknir Reykjavik with a goal aggregate of 14-3.M3 Fylkir vs HK Kópavogur: Fylkir sit in second place in the second division in Iceland. HK come into this game on the back of three successive victories.M4 Keflavik IF vs UMF Stjarnan: Keflavik have won three of their past five outings. Stjarnan are in second place in the Iceland league, seven points behind the leaders.M5 Kordrengir vs Selfoss: Kordrengir’s last three games have all ended in draws. Selfoss are in top place in the Iceland second division on the back of a run of 11 unbeaten games.M6 Valur Rekjavik vs Breidablik: Valur have lost their last four outings. Breidablik have won their first eight games of the new season in Iceland and already have a handy lead.M7 Argentinos Juniors vs Independiente: Argentinos Juniors have lost two of their previous three home games against Independiente.M8 Rosario Central vs Godoy Cruz: Godoy Cruz have won their past two clashes against Rosario Central, both with a 2-1 scoreline.M9 Platense vs Gimnasia La Plata: After two rounds of the new season in Argentina, Platense are the only side with a 100% record. Gimnasia La Plata have not lost in their previous seven encounters.M10 Racing Club vs Velez Sarsfield: Racing have been beaten in three of their past four matches. Velez Sarsfield are unbeaten in their past four meetings with Racing. Suggested permutation: R8.00 1 x 1 x 1 x 2,3 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 2,3